Create & Populate Dimension Tables for AIVideo_DataWarehouse 12

1) Download zip attachment by clicking on this image above 

2) Open SQL Files  and execute each, one by one, (excluding the SQL file for adding keys) to create Fact & Dimension Tables for the Data Warehouse database you'd created in a previous step.

3) Create Data Flow Tasks for these tables.




The following is the SELECT statement used in the StudentDetails OLE DB Source located in the above GIF.

select 
[StudentVideoId]
,[StudentUserId]
,[StudentName]
, LEFT([StartDate], CHARINDEX(' (', [StartDate])) as StartDate
,[CampusLocation]
,[StudentEmail]
,[LastDateModified]
,[LastModifiedBy]
,[VideoCount]
from [dbo].[dic_StudentDetails]
